### Describe the bug
In trying to implement Identity without Entity Framework Core and debugging through the UserManager.cs file I noticed that the Security Stamp is not set when the AccessFailedCount is incremented or when the LockoutEnd value is set.

This means that if you were using the security stamp to determine if the record was changed then it would not be updated.

It is also missing on recovery code changes like `GenerateNewTwoFactorRecoveryCodesAsync` and `RedeemTwoFactorRecoveryCodeAsync`.

This _seems_ to be an oversight.

